Here’s how I make DIY bakery style muffin liners (also known as tulip baking cups). Cut parchment paper into 5.5-inch or 6-inch squares. Cut about 2 inches deep at each midpoint. You’ll end up with a four petals flower shape. Press the cut parchment in the center of each muffin tin, allowing the edges to naturally fold on top of each other. Use your fingers or a cup to press the paper down. Don’t worry if the paper rises a bit. It will naturally sink down once you add batter. *however, if the paper still won’t sink down with batter, that may mean you didn’t the cut deep enough at each midpoint. #bakingtips #littleepicurean #bakinghacks #diymuffinliners

Practice is the only way to get better at something. Here’s how I learned to practice piping with buttercream in culinary school! Grab a round cake pan and turn it upside down. Use this method to practice borders, shells, rosettes, stars, etc. You’re trying to build muscle memory. If you only practice piping in straight lines, you may have a difficult time adjusting to curves when it comes time to pipe on a real cake. When you run out of space on the cake pan, simply scape off all the buttercream and start over again! #buttercream #cakedecorating #caketips

#ad In partnership with @gotmilk I am sharing a twist on one of my favorite holiday recipes. Bibingka is a Filipino rice cake enjoyed during the holiday season. There are many variations of bibingka. Chocolate bibingka is my unique version that I love sharing with my son. It’s made with real milk, rice flour, ap flour, egg, and coconut oil.

Chocolate bibingka is best served warm, fresh from the oven. It’s even better paired with a cup of steamed real milk. It’s a wonderful calming way to slow down and enjoy the holiday season together! Visit GotMilk.com/recipes for more inspiration. #getrealmilk #gotmilk 

Ingredients
1 cup plain rice flour (120 g)
1/4 cup AP flour (35 g)
1/2 cup brown or white sugar (100 g)
1 Tbsp baking powder
1 tsp kosher salt 
1 cup real milk 
1/4 cup melted unrefined coconut oil (60 g)
1 large egg
Chocolate or candy bar of choice 
Salted butter, for brushing 

Instructions 
1. Preheat oven to 375degrees F. Line giant muffin tin with banana leaves.
2. In a large bowl, whisk together rice flour, AP flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt. Add in real milk, coconut oil, and egg. Mix until smooth and well combined.
3. Pour about 1/2 cup of batter into prepared muffin tin. Bake for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and add chocolate. Return to oven and bake for another 5 minutes. Immediately brush with salted butter. Serve warm.

Cranberry mint julep! This is a super strong potent drink that needs to be served with a ton of crushed ice. It’s my kind of holiday cocktail! #holidaydrinks #cranberrycocktail #cocktailrecipes 
8 mint leaves
2 tsp sugar 
1 oz cranberry syrup (or more to taste)
2.5 oz bourbon
Crushed iced! (It melts fast, diluting the drink to the perfect balance)

To make cranberry syrup: bring 1/2 cup water + 1/2 cup sugar to a boil. Add 1 cup fresh cranberries + zest of 1 orange. Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes until cranberries start bursting open. Remove from heat. Transfer to container and chill in fridge. Syrup will have thickened. Strain out cranberries (discard or snack!). Keep syrup in fridge until ready to use.

Pull apart snowflake cinnamon bread! I stumbled upon this technique from @sarahtreed . I used the dough from my funfetti cinnamon roll. Divide the dough into three pieces. Roll each piece into an 11-inch circle. Layer dough with softened butter and cinnamon sugar. Slice round into 16 wedges. Twist two wedges into each other and pinch end seams together. Proof and then bake! You could top it with  cream cheese frosting or keep it simple with a dusting of powdered sugar.

I was gifted this bottle of @selectaperitivousa . It’s a new-to-me Italian aperitif that has completely won me over! This cocktail is called the Select Americano. It’s a refreshing mix between a Negroni and a traditional spritz. You only need three ingredients (perfect for holiday parties)! For an added dimension of flavor, use your favorite flavored sparkling water instead of club soda. 
1.5 oz Select Aperitivo
1.5 oz sweet vermouth
4 oz club soda 
Garnish with green olive and orange slice
